cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the task of detecting satire in news articles using machine learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of linear classifiers, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Learning). The use of large datasets and the evaluation of the models' performance suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for classification indicates that the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of news articles, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
